                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 12.359,
                                "byte_start": 84238,
                                "byte_stop": 133766,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 98-1161, the City of Erie versus Pap\u2019s A.M. will be announced by Justice O\u2019Connor."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 12.359,
                        "stop": 200.777,
                        "byte_start": 133766,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15092,
                            "name": "Sandra Day O\u0027Connor",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/sandra_day_oconnor",
                            "last_name": "O\u0027Connor",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2736,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 370242000,
                                    "date_end": 1138687200,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2736"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32763,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49563,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/sandra_day_oconnor.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8894,
                            "identifier": "sandra_day_oconnor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 12.359,
                                "stop": 17.388,
                                "byte_start": 133766,
                                "byte_stop": 153828,
                                "text": "This case comes here on Writ of Certiorari from the Supreme Court of Pennsylvania."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.388,
                                "stop": 22.693,
                                "byte_start": 153828,
                                "byte_stop": 175040,
                                "text": "The city of Erie, Pennsylvania, enacted an ordinance banning public nudity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.693,
                                "stop": 39.501,
                                "byte_start": 175040,
                                "byte_stop": 242331,
                                "text": "The respondent, Pap\u2019s A.M. which operate at a nude dancing establishment in Erie known as \u201cKandyland\u201d, challenge the constitutionality of the ordinance, claiming that it violated respondents right to Freedom of Expression under the First Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.501,
                                "stop": 46.84,
                                "byte_start": 242331,
                                "byte_stop": 271693,
                                "text": "Pennsylvania Supreme Court held the public nudity sections of the ordinance violated respondent\u0027s First Amendment rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.84,
                                "stop": 54.018,
                                "byte_start": 271693,
                                "byte_stop": 300323,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk of the Court today, we reverse the judgment of the Pennsylvania Supreme Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.018,
                                "stop": 58.002,
                                "byte_start": 300323,
                                "byte_stop": 316310,
                                "text": "As a preliminary matter, we conclude that the case is not moot."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.002,
                                "stop": 67.546,
                                "byte_start": 316310,
                                "byte_stop": 354449,
                                "text": "Although Pap\u2019s is no longer operating \u201cKandyland\u201d as a nude dancing establishment, this is not a \u201crun of the mill voluntary cessation\u201d case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.546,
                                "stop": 72.782,
                                "byte_start": 354449,
                                "byte_stop": 375451,
                                "text": "Here it is the plaintiff who, having prevailed below, seeks to have the case declared moot."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.782,
                                "stop": 80.951,
                                "byte_start": 375451,
                                "byte_stop": 408052,
                                "text": "And it is this defendant city that seeks to invoke the federal judicial power to obtain this Court\u2019s review of the decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.951,
                                "stop": 92.702,
                                "byte_start": 408052,
                                "byte_stop": 455072,
                                "text": "The city has an ongoing injury, which the court can remedy; and to the extent that it has an interest in resuming operations, Pap\u2019s still has a concrete stake in the outcome."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.702,
                                "stop": 105.032,
                                "byte_start": 455072,
                                "byte_stop": 504391,
                                "text": "On the merits, we hold that Erie\u2019s ordinance is a content-neutral regulation that should be evaluated under the intermediate scrutiny standards set forth in United States versus O\u2019Brien."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.032,
                                "stop": 119.913,
                                "byte_start": 504391,
                                "byte_stop": 563951,
                                "text": "Under that standard, a content-neutral regulation will be upheld, if it furthers an important government interest and the incidental restriction on First Amendment freedoms is no greater than essential to the furtherance of that interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.913,
                                "stop": 129.9,
                                "byte_start": 563951,
                                "byte_stop": 603866,
                                "text": "We note that in this case, like the most recent previous nude dancing case we decided, the court has produced a multitude of opinions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.9,
                                "stop": 143.417,
                                "byte_start": 603866,
                                "byte_stop": 657991,
                                "text": "Nevertheless, in an effort to describe the holding, a majority of the court agrees that Erie\u2019s ban on public nudity is content-neutral and must be evaluated under the O\u2019Brien standard."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.417,
                                "stop": 153.516,
                                "byte_start": 657991,
                                "byte_stop": 698325,
                                "text": "The ordinance, by its terms, regulates conduct, not speech, and it bans all public nudity regardless whether it\u2019s accompanied by expressive activity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.516,
                                "stop": 169.66,
                                "byte_start": 698325,
                                "byte_stop": 762899,
                                "text": "As the Pennsylvania Court construed the language in the preamble, one purpose of the ordinance is to combat the negative secondary effects, such as crime and other threats to public health and safety that are caused by the presence of nude dancing establishments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.66,
                                "stop": 183.936,
                                "byte_start": 762899,
                                "byte_stop": 820055,
                                "text": "Although there is only a plurality of the Court, which would hold that the ordinance satisfies all four parts of the O\u2019Brien test, six members of the court agree that the judgment below must be reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 183.936,
                                "stop": 200.777,
                                "byte_start": 820055,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment, which Justice Thomas has joined; Justice Souter has filed an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part; Justice Stevens has filed a dissenting opinion which Justice Ginsburg has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
